domain_key|pattern_key|narrowing_key|priority|narrowing_title|narrowing_text|missing_range_signal_key|status|lookup_key
leadership-approach|process_results_vision_people|narrowing_1|1|When the method keeps absorbing attention|Process can narrow when the way of working keeps being refined after there is enough clarity to act. The work may feel orderly, but the next decision, future reason, or people conversation can wait too long.|people|active|leadership-approach::process_results_vision_people::narrowing_1
leadership-approach|process_results_vision_people|narrowing_2|2|When Process and Results take most of the space|Process and Results can narrow together when the combination of sequence, standards, and dependable handover with decision, ownership, and follow-through answers the first questions too quickly. The pattern may look productive, but it can leave less room for a stronger future frame and reason for the work or clearer communication, inclusion, and relational judgement until the work is harder to adjust.|vision|active|leadership-approach::process_results_vision_people::narrowing_2
leadership-approach|process_results_vision_people|narrowing_3|3|Before People is added|Vision can add range before People is brought in deliberately, but the pattern may still narrow if People is left until later. The likely miss is progress that looks organised from the outside while commitment, confidence, or shared understanding needs more attention, especially when Process and Results already feel convincing.|people|active|leadership-approach::process_results_vision_people::narrowing_3
